# The results of this example can be compared by results in the follwoing paper: 
#"High-accuracy Monte Carlo study of the three-dimensional classical Heisenberg ferromagnet", Phys. Rev. B 43, 6087


1) run 
   mc.x -inp1 cubic
2) add Jij value in Parameters_Jij block of  cubic.inp2.mcin file

  Begin Parameters_Jij
   t1=  1:t2=  1:sh= 1:Jij= 0.00300!:sig=?????!:d= 5.29177211
  End Parameters_Jij
   
3) Uncomment any other parameters that you want to be calculated in monte carlo simulations 
4) run 
   mc.x -inp2 cubic
5) edit temperatures, supercell size according to what you want in cubic.mcin file
6) run
   mc.x cubic
